    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_E41A2450-22E1-0135-9DE3-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>By default, the SpeedGrader <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-use-the-student-list-to-view-student-submissions-in/ta-p/770" target="_blank">student list</a> arranges student names alphabetically by last name. For easier grading, you can sort the student list by student name (alphabetically), submission date, or by submission status. You can also view the students in random order and view the students within a submission status in random order.</p>
  </div>
</div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open_speedgrader" data-step-uuid="429edc9b-fb42-4650-8e07-f7a9ff169ed5">
    <h2 id="open_speedgrader" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Open SpeedGrader</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/008/338/038/original/a0f4f03c-4fec-44ef-be4c-2aac414f509d.png" srcset="" alt="Open SpeedGrader" height="78" width="282">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_E41AFDA0-22E1-0135-9DE5-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Open SpeedGrader from any assignment, graded discussion, or quiz.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open_speedgrader_settings" data-step-uuid="4A765A78-F96E-407B-A19A-862274B3493F">
    <h2 id="open_speedgrader_settings" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Open SpeedGrader Options</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/008/338/040/original/33803b4d-6689-4917-ae67-dd2bd628db0b.png" srcset="" alt="Open SpeedGrader Options" height="206" width="343">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_E41C0E40-22E1-0135-9DE7-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>To open SpeedGrader options, click the <strong>Settings</strong> icon [1]. In the settings drop-down menu, click the <strong>Options </strong>link [2]. </p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="sort_student_list" data-step-uuid="500BC54A-B1F7-4454-808B-066FD489648D">
    <h2 id="sort_student_list" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Sort Student List</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/008/338/042/original/5f7b1cfb-8212-4062-8c7e-46f9f79c1b78.png" srcset="" alt="Sort Student List" height="283" width="409">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_E41C5C00-22E1-0135-9DE9-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>To open the sorting options for the student list, click the <strong>Sort student list </strong>drop-down menu.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
        <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-2" id="select_sorting_option" data-step-uuid="3D2F98FA-751D-4A8D-A5CE-DFD813D6CCA3">
    <h3 id="select_sorting_option" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Select Sorting Option</h3>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/008/359/259/original/4e1c7b5a-7b41-4571-b52e-f91beeec8f99.png" srcset="" alt="Select Sorting Option" height="313" width="551">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_E41C9160-22E1-0135-9DEB-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Select the sorting option you prefer for the student list. </p>
<p>You can choose to sort by student name (alphabetically), the date they submitted the assignment, by submission status (needs grading, not submitted, etc.). You can also randomize the order of students or randomize students within a submission status.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>
 
  </div>

